## 2. Composable Safety Policies

Define how safety policies compose using category theory:
- Product composition: PolicyA ∧ PolicyB (both must approve)
- Coproduct: PolicyA ∨ PolicyB (either can approve)
- Sequential: PolicyA ; PolicyB (A then B)
- Conditional: if condition then PolicyA else PolicyB

```rust
/// Composable safety policy combinators.
pub enum PolicyCombinator {
    /// Both policies must approve (conjunction).
    Product(Box<dyn Policy>, Box<dyn Policy>),
    /// Either policy can approve (disjunction).
    Coproduct(Box<dyn Policy>, Box<dyn Policy>),
    /// Sequential: first policy then second.
    Sequential(Box<dyn Policy>, Box<dyn Policy>),
    /// Conditional: select policy based on predicate.
    Conditional {
        predicate: Box<dyn Fn(&[Signal]) -> bool>,
        if_true: Box<dyn Policy>,
        if_false: Box<dyn Policy>,
    },
}
```

## 3. Safety-Aware Model Routing

Extend CascadeRouter with safety-aware model selection:
- High-risk actions → stronger model (T2)
- Safety-critical decisions → dual-model verification (CaMeL)
- Low-risk reads → fast model (T0 deterministic or T1)

